<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ870324-0077 </DOCNO><HL> Who's News:Bally's Scientific UnitNames Bower, Koza,Others to New Posts</HL><DD> 03/24/87</DD><SO> WALL STREET JOURNAL (J)</SO><IN> WNEWS BLY </IN><DATELINE> CHICAGO  </DATELINE><TEXT>   Bally Manufacturing Corp. said its Scientific Games Inc. subsidiary named several executives to new positions in a management reorganization.    Daniel W. Bower, 54 years old, president and a co-founder of the unit, was named to the added posts of chairman and chief executive officer, effective April 1.    He succeeds John R. Koza, also a co-founder of the unit, who was named chairman emeritus. Mr. Koza, 43 years old, has said he wants to play a less-active role in day-to-day operations. He also will be a consultant to Bally, a hotel and casino operator, and to Scientific Games; the subsidiary sells lottery products and services.    The subsidiary also named a three-man executive committee, which will have &quot;primary operational responsibility for day-to-day operations.&quot; The committee consists of: Robert L. Mote, 37, executive vice president and chief legal officer; John C. Pittman, 37, executive vice president of the company's instant game and lottery consulting operations in the U.S.; and William F. Behm, 43, an executive vice president of computerized lottery operations. </TEXT></DOC>